OL,3,C'It's been hell': Doctor wins legal
OL,4,Cbattle over 'flawed' work report
OL,6,FResidents then went to Guernsey's
OL,7,FMedical Director, Dr Rabey, who
OL,8,Fordered a second investigation which
OL,9,Fdecided Dr Borchardt was at fault,
OL,10,Fbefore it was eventually determined
OL,11,Fthat this had not been carried out
OL,12,Fproperly.
OL,14,FThe case went to court after Dr
OL,15,FBorchardt applied for judicial review
OL,16,Fover the second investigation, stating
OL,17,Fit was an "abuse of process" and
OL,18,F"flawed and incomplete".
